---
// components
import Container from "../../elements/Container.astro";
import Heading from "../../elements/Heading.astro";
import Text from "../../elements/Text.astro";
import ContainerBottom from "../../elements/ContainerBottom.astro";

// assets
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import sysAd from "../../../assets/OJT/SysAd.png";
import netAd from "../../../assets/OJT/NetAd.png";
import endUser from "../../../assets/OJT/EndUser.png";

import beyondBreach from "../../../assets/Certificates/Beyond the breach.jpg";
import beyondCode from "../../../assets/Certificates/Beyond the Code.png";
import cyberSocPH from "../../../assets/Certificates/CyberSocPH.png";
import decodeData from "../../../assets/Certificates/Decode the data.png";
import digitalTransformation from "../../../assets/Certificates/Digital Transformation.png";
import headInClouds from "../../../assets/Certificates/Head in the Clouds.png";

// content
const softSkills = [
    "Critical Thinking",
    "Leadership",
    "Presentations",
    "Creativity",
    "Problem Solving",
    "Initiative"
];

const technicalSkills = [
    { category: "Coding Languages", items: "Python, C++" },
    { category: "Backend Development", items: "Supabase" },
    { category: "Database", items: "PostgreSQL, Oracle Database" },
    { category: "UI Development", items: "HTML5, Flutter, Figma" }
];

const certifications = [
    { src: beyondBreach, alt: "Beyond the Breach" },
    { src: beyondCode, alt: "Beyond the Code" },
    { src: cyberSocPH, alt: "CyberSocPH" },
    { src: decodeData, alt: "Decode the Data" },
    { src: digitalTransformation, alt: "Digital Transformation" },
    { src: headInClouds, alt: "Head in the Clouds" }
];
---

<Container variant={'md'}>
    <Heading tagName="h2" tagSize="h2" class="text-center">Experience</Heading>

    <!-- Skills -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <Container class="flex flex-col gap-6 p-6 border-3 border-base-900">
            <div>
                <Heading tagName="h3" tagSize="h4">Soft Skills</Heading>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-3">
                    {softSkills.map((skill) => (
                        <span class="px-3 py-1 border-2 border-base-900 text-base-900 text-sm">{skill}</span>
                    ))}
                </div>
            </div>
            <div>
                <Heading tagName="h3" tagSize="h4">Technical Skills</Heading>
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 mt-3">
                    {technicalSkills.map((group) => (
                        <Text variant={'sm'} class="text-base-900">
                            <strong>{group.category}:</strong> {group.items}
                        </Text>
                    ))}
                </div>
            </div>
        </Container>
        <ContainerBottom />
    </div>

    <!-- OJT Journey -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
        <Heading tagName="h3" tagSize="h3" class="text-center">OJT Journey</Heading>

        <!-- System Admin -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <Heading tagName="h4" tagSize="h3">System Admin</Heading>
            <Image src={sysAd} alt="System Admin" class="w-full h-auto border-3 border-base-900" />
            <Text variant={'sm'} class="text-base-900">
                During my time on the infrastructure team, a core responsibility involved managing and monitoring
                local server infrastructure directly inside the enterprise data centers. To support the high volume
                of automated data processing across the network, I handled routine tape reloading operations, which
                served as a crucial pillar for the company's disaster recovery and offline backup storage strategies.
                Using terminal utilities like Remote Desktop Connection Manager (RDCMan) from a secure station, I
                regularly executed command-line data migration operations to ensure continuous storage optimization
                and maintain high data availability.
            </Text>
        </div>

        <!-- Network Admin -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <Heading tagName="h4" tagSize="h3">Network Admin</Heading>
            <Image src={netAd} alt="Network Admin" class="w-full h-auto border-3 border-base-900" />
            <Text variant={'sm'} class="text-base-900">
                My responsibilities under the network administration function focused heavily on responding to
                localized connectivity tickets, physical layer media maintenance, and live traffic analysis. A
                significant portion of this role involved structural cable management and handling network switches
                directly within the server racks, where I organized dense patch panels and managed network
                connections to maintain clear infrastructure layouts. I also performed hands-on hardware procedures,
                including UTP cable crimping and verification testing using specialized tone generators and digital
                cable analyzers, to ensure line integrity and minimal signal loss at individual user drop points.
            </Text>
            <Text variant={'sm'} class="text-base-900">
                On the logical side, I regularly assisted with port activation and packet tracing tasks to resolve
                routing bottlenecks and patch connections for various departments. Using command-line tools like
                PuTTY, I interfaced with managed switches to modify VLAN configurations and activate specific ports
                based on incoming support requests. This balance of physical infrastructure management and
                software-defined network troubleshooting provided a solid foundation in maintaining enterprise-grade
                network reliability and speed.
            </Text>
        </div>

        <!-- End User Support -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <Heading tagName="h4" tagSize="h3">End User Support</Heading>
            <Image src={endUser} alt="End User Support" class="w-full h-auto border-3 border-base-900" />
            <Text variant={'sm'} class="text-base-900">
                In the End User Support role, I acted as a direct line of technical assistance for workplace hardware
                deployment, device diagnostics, and thorough lifecycle tracking. This involved performing
                comprehensive hardware troubleshooting on corporate machines, which required dismantling laptops to
                diagnose component failures, clean internal cooling systems, and upgrade modular parts like storage
                drives or keyboards. By regularly working on the hardware layout of enterprise laptops, I developed a
                strong familiarity with device assembly standards and component testing.
            </Text>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Certifications -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <Heading tagName="h3" tagSize="h3" class="text-center">Certifications</Heading>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            {certifications.map((cert) => (
                <div class="border-3 border-base-900">
                    <Image src={cert.src} alt={cert.alt} class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
                </div>
            ))}
        </div>
        <ContainerBottom />
    </div>

</Container>